# Environment Variables for Local Testing
# ========================================
# This file is for LOCAL TESTING ONLY. 
# For GitHub Actions, use repository secrets instead.

# GitHub Personal Access Token
# -----------------------------
# This is the same token as your RELEASE_PAT in GitHub Secrets
# Used for: Automated releases and protected branch access
# Generate at: https://github.com/settings/tokens/new
# 
# Required scopes (Classic Token):
# - repo (Full control of private repositories)
# - workflow (optional - if workflows are modified)
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# NPM Token (Optional)
# --------------------
# Only needed if testing NPM publishing locally
# Generate at: https://www.npmjs.com/settings/YOUR_USERNAME/tokens
# Required: "Packages and scopes: Read and write" permission
NPM_TOKEN=npm_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Note: RELEASE_PAT vs GITHUB_TOKEN
# ----------------------------------
# - RELEASE_PAT: Name used in GitHub Secrets (repository settings)
# - GITHUB_TOKEN: Variable name used locally and in scripts
# - They should contain the same PAT value